DTEND:20260602T173000Z
SUMMARY:Summer 2026 Workshop Series: RIP "Final_v2_ACTUAL_FINAL": Organizin
 g Your Research Like a Pro
DESCRIPTION:Organized by: ["Provost's Office"\, 'Beyond The Classroom'\, 'D
 ivision of Student Affairs']\\nCategory: Lecture/Panel Discussion\\nTuesda
 ys and Thursdays in Sci 101 from 12-1:30pm. Lunch will be provided. Stop s
 earching for "Final_v2_ACTUAL_FINAL" and start researching! This workshop 
 covers the "hidden curriculum" of digital research—from professional fil
 e naming and Google Drive organization to advanced collaboration technique
 s. We’ll start with the basics of digital hygiene and finish with an int
 roduction to the College’s High-Performance Computing (HPC) resources fo
 r those ready to scale up their data.  Presented by Jen Moore\, Academic 
 Technologist for the Arts & Humanities\, ITS.  \\nDetails: https://swatce
 ntral.swarthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid%3D1395671872
